{"questionId":"6091","questionHtml":"<p>An electron of mass <em>m</em><sub><em>e </em></sub>orbits an alpha particle of mass <em>m</em><sub><em>α </em></sub>in a circular orbit of radius <em>r</em>. Which expression gives the speed of the electron?</p>\n<p>A. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{2k{e^2}}}{{{m_e}r}}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mi>k</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>B. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{2k{e^2}}}{{{m_a}r}}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n        <mi>k</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>C. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{4k{e^2}}}{{{m_e}r}}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n        <mi>k</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>D. &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\sqrt {\\frac{{4k{e^2}}}{{{m_a}r}}} \">\n  <msqrt>\n    <mfrac>\n      <mrow>\n        <mn>4</mn>\n        <mi>k</mi>\n        <mrow>\n          <msup>\n            <mi>e</mi>\n            <mn>2</mn>\n          </msup>\n        </mrow>\n      </mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <mrow>\n          <msub>\n            <mi>m</mi>\n            <mi>a</mi>\n          </msub>\n        </mrow>\n        <mi>r</mi>\n      </mrow>\n    </mfrac>\n  </msqrt>\n</math></span></p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>A</p>","meta":{"questionId":"6091","referenceCode":"18M.1.HL.TZ1.32","subjectId":"46-dp-physics-last-assessment-2024","title":"An electron of mass me orbits an alpha particle of mass mα in a circular orbit of radius r. Which expression gives the speed of the electron? A. 2 k e 2 m e r B. 2 k e 2 m a r C. 4","paper":"1","level":"HL","questionNumber":"32","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 1]","breadcrumbLabels":["Additional higher level (AHL)","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields","10.2 – Fields at work","Additional higher level (AHL)","Topic 10: Fields"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}